Observations from Fig. 4 indicate that RLIM successfully fits the reported data records from mid-November until mid-January and provides predictions for the upcoming weeks. Delving into the 2 columns of Fig. 4, a conclusion can be drawn that different assignments to the secondary infection rate will result in different outcomes and prediction series. For example, a \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
